b'[<p><i><b>UFC 99: The Comeback</b></i> was a <a href="/wiki/Mixed_martial_arts" title="Mixed martial arts">mixed martial arts</a> event held by the <a href="/wiki/Ultimate_Fighting_Championship" title="Ultimate Fighting Championship">Ultimate Fighting Championship</a> (UFC) on June 13, 2009 in <a href="/wiki/Cologne" title="Cologne">Cologne</a>, <a href="/wiki/Germany" title="Germany">Germany</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-UFC99_3-0"><a href="#cite_note-UFC99-3">[3]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>This event was the first UFC event held in Germany,<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-4"><a href="#cite_note-4">[4]</a></sup> as well as the first in mainland Europe (events have previously been held in the United Kingdom, Ireland, Canada, the continental United States, Brazil, and Japan).\n</p>, <p>On Monday, June 1, the UFC announced that <a href="/wiki/Mirko_Cro_Cop" title="Mirko Cro Cop">Mirko Cro Cop</a> would be returning to the promotion to face <a href="/wiki/Mostapha_al-Turk" title="Mostapha al-Turk">Mostapha al-Turk</a> at <i>UFC 99</i>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-ufccrocop_5-0"><a href="#cite_note-ufccrocop-5">[5]</a></sup> It was Cro Cop\'s first fight in the UFC since his unanimous-decision loss to <a href="/wiki/Cheick_Kongo" title="Cheick Kongo">Cheick Kongo</a> at <i><a href="/wiki/UFC_75" title="UFC 75">UFC 75</a></i> in 2007.\n</p>, <p>An announced bout between <a href="/wiki/Heath_Herring" title="Heath Herring">Heath Herring</a> and <a href="/wiki/Cain_Velasquez" title="Cain Velasquez">Cain Velasquez</a> was cancelled due to an illness that Herring was suffering. On May 20, 2009, <a href="/wiki/Cheick_Kongo" title="Cheick Kongo">Cheick Kongo</a> was announced as the replacement.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-kongo_6-0"><a href="#cite_note-kongo-6">[6]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>Fighters were awarded $60,000 bonuses.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-7"><a href="#cite_note-7">[7]</a></sup>\n</p>]'